cs.DB, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.PL, cs.SE 

This paper deals with dynamic data management systems and query optimization techniques, which are core topics in the field of database systems (cs.DB). The paper also discusses parallelization and optimization frameworks, which are relevant to distributed computing (cs.DC) and algorithm design and analysis (cs.DS). The use of heuristics and cost-based optimization techniques suggests a focus on programming languages and compilers (cs.PL), while the development of a prototype system for dynamic data management involves software engineering (cs.SE).
